            <h2>Answers</h2>
            <article id="accessibility-answers-1" class="well">
              <h3>Can I navigate on the website, using just the keyboard?</h3>
              Yes, you can. In order to navigate using the keyboard, you can use these combinations of keys:
              <ul class="light-keys">
                <li>
                  <kbd>SPACE</kbd> to scroll down
                </li>
                <li>
                  <kbd>Up</kbd> <kbd>Down</kbd> <kbd>Left</kbd> <kbd>Right</kbd> arrows to scroll in that direction
                </li>
              </ul>
              <ul class="light-keys">
                <li>
                  <kbd>TAB</kbd> to start focusing an element and to focus the next element
                </li>
                <li>
                  <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>TAB</kbd> to focus the previous element
                </li>
                <li>
                  An element which is focused has a blue border around it.
                  <ul class="light-keys">
                    <li>
                      <kbd>Space</kbd> to choose a focused element
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <kbd>Enter</kbd> to access the focused element
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <br />
                  <figure>
                    <figcaption>Here, <i>Modify</i> is focused</figcaption>
                    <img class="img-responsive img-thumbnail" src="/static/img/static/accessibility/example-focused-element.jpg" alt="Example of an element focused" />
                  </figure>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </article>
            <article id="accessibility-answers-2" class="well">
              <h3>Do you provide shortcuts?</h3>
              Yes, we do. <br />This is a list of useful shortcuts:
              <ul>
                <li> All pages
                  <ul class="light-keys">
                    <li>
                      <kbd>ALT</kbd> + <kbd>A</kbd> - Wisply goes to accessibility page
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <kbd>ALT</kbd> + <kbd>W</kbd> - Wisply goes to home page
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <kbd>ALT</kbd> + <kbd>C</kbd> - Wisply goes contact page
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <kbd>ALT</kbd> + <kbd>Z</kbd> - Activates the main search
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li> When you are connected
                  <ul class="light-keys">
                    <li>
                      <kbd>ALT</kbd> + <kbd>L</kbd>  - Wisply logs you out
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
